<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(a)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>&quot;Able-bodied adult
without dependents (ABAWD)&quot; means <a name="_Hlk169513557">a recipient who
is at least age 18 but younger than age 55 </a>who does not have dependents and
is subject to special work requirements <span class=GramE>in order to</span>
receive supplemental nutrition assistance program (SNAP) benefits.</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.25in'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-indent:.5in'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(b)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>“Agency error” means </span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#010100;
background:white'>an action or lack of action by the department resulting in
the underpayment or an overpayment of an applicant or recipient’s level of
benefit or resulting in an incorrect determination of eligibility or
ineligibility. This term includes “</span><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>administrative error (AE)”.</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-1.2pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in;tab-stops:.75in 78.0pt 102.0pt 1.75in 150.0pt 210.0pt'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(c)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>“Alien” means an individual who is not a
citizen of the United States.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:2.15pt;margin-bottom:
0in;margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-add-space:auto;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(d)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>“Application” means a
formal request for assistance or services pursuant to RSA 167:8, which is
signed and dated by an individual or authorized representative.</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.25in'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(e)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span></span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Assistance group
(AG)” means <span style='color:black'>individuals living together whose needs,
income, and resources are considered and <span class=GramE>combined together</span>
when determining eligibility or the <span class=GramE>amount</span> of
benefits.</span></span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.25in'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(f)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span></span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Authorized
representative (AR)” means an individual acting on behalf of the&nbsp;<span
class=SpellE>casehead</span>&nbsp;in some or <span class=GramE>all of</span>&nbsp;the&nbsp;aspects
of initial and continuing eligibility.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.25in'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(g)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span><span style='color:black'>“Best estimate”
means an expectation of income to be received by an individual determined by
evaluating past, present, and anticipated significant and non-significant
income changes.</span></span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.25in'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(h)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span></span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“<span
class=SpellE>Casehead</span>” means the individual under whose name the case is
listed.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.25in'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:2.15pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(<span class=SpellE>i</span>)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> 
</span></span><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Department”
means the New Hampshire (NH) department of health and human services (DHHS).</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:8.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(j)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>“Educational income” means financial
assistance, payments, loans, reimbursements, or allowances paid to or on behalf
of post-secondary education students.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

