<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(a)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>“Personal identification number (PIN)” means
the 4-digit number used by an individual to activate and control the use of the
EBT card. </span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial'>(b)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>“Probation and parole violators” <span
class=GramE>means</span> individuals who are violating a condition of probation
or parole under federal or state law.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(c)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>&quot;Questionable&quot; means any written or
oral statement by an applicant or recipient, which is inconsistent with other
statements made by the same individual, inconsistent with information provided
on current or past applications for assistance, or inconsistent with
information received by the department from other sources.</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(d)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> 
</span>“Recipient identification number (RID)” means a number assigned to an
individual who is currently receiving benefits or was previously receiving
benefits.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

