Eligibility for Able-Bodied Adults Without Dependents<o:p></o:p></u></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:27.35pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>.</span><span style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ConvertStyle19 align=left style='text-align:left'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(a)
Pursuant to 7 CFR 273.24(d)(1)(iv), an able-bodied adult without dependents
(ABAWD), who has received three countable months of supplemental nutrition
assistance program benefits, may regain eligibility if they verify that within
30 days <span class=GramE>subsequent to</span> application they will:</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ConvertStyle19 align=left style='text-align:left'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(1)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>Work 80 or more hours;</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ConvertStyle19 align=left style='text-align:left'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(2)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>Participate in and
comply with the requirements of a work program for 80 or more hours; </span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ConvertStyle19 align=left style='text-align:left'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(3)<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>Perform any combination of work and
participation in a work program for 80 or more hours; or</span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ConvertStyle19 align=left style='text-align:left'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;text-indent:
.5in'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>(4)<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>Become exempt from
ABAWD work requirements, pursuant to 7 CFR 273.24(c). </span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ConvertStyle19 align=left style='text-align:left'><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(b)
Pursuant to 7 CFR 273.24(d)(2)(<span class=SpellE>i</span>), an ABAWD who is
regaining eligibility by working, participating in a work program, or a
combination of both for 80 hours, shall have benefits prorated from the date of
application.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span></span><span
style='font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

